NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, operate under the influence -7th offense.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss count 2 as a matter of law and moves to dismiss and read in count 3.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, consecutive to any sentence presently being served.
The defendant is not eligible for either program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2)	AODA assessment and follow through;
3)	Maintain absolute sobriety;
4)	Pay a $600.00 fine plus costs, plus $20.00 blood draw, total of $1,839.00;
5)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6)	provide DNA sample;
7)	maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination.
In addition, the Court orders a thirty-six (36) month DL revocation and period of Ignition Interlock.
Minutes.
